      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tales From Aloft</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Cynthia S Pader letter on David Leonhardt's June 25 travel article recalls long waits on Northwest Airlines check-in lines (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Nowhere in the ''To Do'' list with David Leonhardt's article ''Promises in the Sky'' (June 25) did I see any promise by the airlines to expedite the movement and handling of people on the check-in-lines.</p>
        <p>Last summer, my husband and I waited over an hour on check-in lines at Northwest Airlines terminals at both La Guardia and San Francisco airports for cross-continent flights on planes that were not jumbo jets.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Nowhere in the ''To Do'' list with David Leonhardt's article ''Promises in the Sky'' (June 25) did I see any promise by the airlines to expedite the movement and handling of people on the check-in-lines.</p>
        <p>Last summer, my husband and I waited over an hour on check-in lines at Northwest Airlines terminals at both La Guardia and San Francisco airports for cross-continent flights on planes that were not jumbo jets.</p>
        <p>I've just read about a proposed Airbus that is to carry about 550 passengers. Will they have to line up the night before take-off for check-in?</p>
        <p>CYNTHIA S. PADER  Bronx, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
